                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7529: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-26T12:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1926—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received July 26—7:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>304. Following from American consul general at Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 23, noon. I assume Changsha and Hankow consuls are able to keep you
                            advised respecting military situation. Canton army appears to be
                            advancing rapidly and local leaders are now predicting early capture of
                            Hankow and Wuchang. General Chiang<note n="15" xml:id="d456fn15">Chiang
                                Kai-shek, commander in chief of the Cantonese Northern Expedition;
                                also known as Chiang Kai-shih and Chiang Chung-cheng.</note> of
                            Whampoa Cadets is expected to leave Canton in a few days for Hunan.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
